snippets.title: ClusterManager listClusters Sample
snippets.description: Lists all clusters owned by a project in either the specified zone or all zones.

snippets.title: ClusterManager getCluster Sample
snippets.description: Gets the details of a specific cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager createCluster Sample
snippets.description: Creates a cluster, consisting of the specified number and type of Google Compute Engine instances. By default, the cluster is created in the project's [default network](https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/networks-and-firewalls#networks). One firewall is added for the cluster. After cluster creation, the Kubelet creates routes for each node to allow the containers on that node to communicate with all other instances in the cluster. Finally, an entry is added to the project's global metadata indicating which CIDR range the cluster is using.

snippets.title: ClusterManager updateCluster Sample
snippets.description: Updates the settings of a specific cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager updateNodePool Sample
snippets.description: Updates the version and/or image type for the specified node pool.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setNodePoolAutoscaling Sample
snippets.description: Sets the autoscaling settings for the specified node pool.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setLoggingService Sample
snippets.description: Sets the logging service for a specific cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setMonitoringService Sample
snippets.description: Sets the monitoring service for a specific cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setAddonsConfig Sample
snippets.description: Sets the addons for a specific cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setLocations Sample
snippets.description: Sets the locations for a specific cluster. Deprecated. Use [projects.locations.clusters.update](https://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.clusters/update) instead.

snippets.title: ClusterManager updateMaster Sample
snippets.description: Updates the master for a specific cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setMasterAuth Sample
snippets.description: Sets master auth materials. Currently supports changing the admin password or a specific cluster, either via password generation or explicitly setting the password.

snippets.title: ClusterManager deleteCluster Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the cluster, including the Kubernetes endpoint and all worker nodes. Firewalls and routes that were configured during cluster creation are also deleted. Other Google Compute Engine resources that might be in use by the cluster, such as load balancer resources, are not deleted if they weren't present when the cluster was initially created.

snippets.title: ClusterManager listOperations Sample
snippets.description: Lists all operations in a project in a specific zone or all zones.

snippets.title: ClusterManager getOperation Sample
snippets.description: Gets the specified operation.

snippets.title: ClusterManager cancelOperation Sample
snippets.description: Cancels the specified operation.

snippets.title: ClusterManager getServerConfig Sample
snippets.description: Returns configuration info about the Google Kubernetes Engine service.

snippets.title: ClusterManager getJSONWebKeys Sample
snippets.description: Gets the public component of the cluster signing keys in JSON Web Key format. This API is not yet intended for general use, and is not available for all clusters.

snippets.title: ClusterManager listNodePools Sample
snippets.description: Lists the node pools for a cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager getNodePool Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves the requested node pool.

snippets.title: ClusterManager createNodePool Sample
snippets.description: Creates a node pool for a cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager deleteNodePool Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a node pool from a cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager rollbackNodePoolUpgrade Sample
snippets.description: Rolls back a previously Aborted or Failed NodePool upgrade. This makes no changes if the last upgrade successfully completed.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setNodePoolManagement Sample
snippets.description: Sets the NodeManagement options for a node pool.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setLabels Sample
snippets.description: Sets labels on a cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setLegacyAbac Sample
snippets.description: Enables or disables the ABAC authorization mechanism on a cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager startIPRotation Sample
snippets.description: Starts master IP rotation.

snippets.title: ClusterManager completeIPRotation Sample
snippets.description: Completes master IP rotation.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setNodePoolSize Sample
snippets.description: Sets the size for a specific node pool. The new size will be used for all replicas, including future replicas created by modifying [NodePool.locations][google.container.v1.NodePool.locations].

snippets.title: ClusterManager setNetworkPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Enables or disables Network Policy for a cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager setMaintenancePolicy Sample
snippets.description: Sets the maintenance policy for a cluster.

snippets.title: ClusterManager listUsableSubnetworks Sample
snippets.description: Lists subnetworks that are usable for creating clusters in a project.
